---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Ongoing Bookkeeping Greece | Taxomade">
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="mb-16 border-b border-slate-100 pb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tight">Your Greek bookkeeping and tax <span class="text-blue-800">—</span> fully handled, in English.</h1>
      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-slate-600 mb-8 max-w-3xl">Stay compliant every month without touching Greek bureaucracy. We take care of it all.</p>
      <a href="/#configurator" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold rounded-lg text-white bg-slate-900 hover:bg-blue-800 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-sm">
        Start your bookkeeping
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- What it is -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">What it is</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Once you register as a freelancer/self-employed in Greece and become a tax resident, you have ongoing obligations: monthly <strong class="text-slate-900">myDATA</strong> reporting, <strong class="text-slate-900">EFKA</strong> social-security contributions, <strong class="text-slate-900">VAT</strong> returns, your annual tax return, and — <strong class="text-slate-900">mandatory from October 2026</strong> — structured <strong class="text-slate-900">e-invoicing</strong>. We handle all of it through our licensed local accountant, in plain English, so you stay compliant without the stress.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-100 p-6 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">This page covers two cases:</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Freelancers / self-employed:</strong> full <strong>monthly</strong> bookkeeping & compliance (the ongoing service).</li>
          <li><strong>Remote employees</strong> (employed by a company abroad): typically only an <strong>annual Greek tax return</strong>, not full monthly bookkeeping.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Requirements -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-4 text-lg text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>For monthly bookkeeping: you're registered as a freelancer/self-employed in Greece (we handle that registration too).</li>
        <li>An AFM (we set this up first if you don't have one).</li>
        <li>For remote employees: tax residency in Greece (183+ days) triggering an annual return.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- How it works -->
    <section class="mb-16 bg-slate-50 p-8 md:p-10 rounded-2xl border border-slate-100">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">How it works</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center"><span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-slate-900 text-white flex items-center justify-center mr-3 text-sm">1</span> What you do</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 ml-11">Send us your invoices/income info (simple monthly upload); we do the rest.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center"><span class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-800 text-white flex items-center justify-center mr-3 text-sm">2</span> What Taxomade does</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 ml-11">Our licensed Greek accountant handles your freelancer registration, monthly myDATA submissions, EFKA, VAT returns, year-end accounts, the annual tax return, and sets up compliant e-invoicing (mandatory from Oct 2026). You get plain-English summaries and a single point of contact.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-slate-500 mt-8 text-sm italic">Billed as a simple <strong>monthly subscription</strong>.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-8">FAQ</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Do I really need an accountant in Greece?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">For freelancers, ongoing reporting (myDATA, EFKA, VAT) is effectively mandatory and in Greek — almost everyone uses an accountant.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">What about the new e-invoicing in 2026?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">From October 2026, structured B2B e-invoicing via myDATA becomes mandatory. We set it up and manage it for you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">I'm a remote employee, not a freelancer — what do I need?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Usually just an annual Greek tax return, which we handle — not the full monthly service.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">How much does it cost?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">A simple monthly subscription; the exact price depends on your situation — request a quote.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-2">Can you also handle my 5C tax break?</h4>
          <p class="text-lg text-slate-700">Yes — we combine it with your bookkeeping so everything's in one place.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer Disclaimer -->
    <div class="mt-20 pt-8 border-t border-slate-200 text-sm text-slate-500">
      <p>Taxomade is not a government body. We coordinate licensed local accountants and lawyers. Information is general and not individual legal or tax advice.</p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
